# 🏦 Hands-On RAG #2: Production Q&A Bot with OpenSearch & Bedrock

## 📚 Financial Domain: Document Upload Q&A System

### What You'll Build:
A production-ready RAG system that:
- Accepts uploaded financial documents (PDFs, text files)
- Stores embeddings in Amazon OpenSearch
- Uses AWS Bedrock models (Titan Embeddings + Claude)
- Provides accurate answers with source citations
- Handles multi-document queries

### Technologies:
- **Vector Store**: Amazon OpenSearch (managed, scalable)
- **Embeddings**: Amazon Titan Embed Text V2 (1024 dimensions)
- **LLM**: Claude Haiku 4.5 (fast, cost-effective)
- **Framework**: LangChain + Boto3

### Use Case:
**Banking Document Q&A Bot** - Upload financial reports, loan agreements, compliance docs, and ask questions!

### Learning Objectives:
1. ✅ Set up AWS Bedrock clients
2. ✅ Configure Amazon OpenSearch for vector search
3. ✅ Process and upload PDF documents
4. ✅ Implement production-ready RAG pipeline
5. ✅ Build interactive Q&A bot
6. ✅ Handle errors and edge cases
7. ✅ Monitor costs and performance

